    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-29T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-29T18:00:00-05:00" n="459"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d459">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/8275</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_MIN1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-29T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 29, 1917, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>471. Your 1221, December 24, 3 p.m. Respecting matter of submarines, see
                    Department’s memorandum of August 31, 1916, in reply to Allied memorandum of
                    August 21, 1916, regarding status of submarines,<note n="1" xml:id="d459fn1">
                        <ref target="frus1916Supp#pg_769">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1916, Supplement, pp.
                            769</ref>–<ref target="frus1916Supp#pg_771">771</ref>.</note> published
                    in White Books. You may say to your colleagues that as this Government is not in
                    a position to change its views as then expressed, you will be unable to join
                    them in representations, unless the cases involve a violation of neutrality. In
                    such cases report facts fully to Department and make no representations without
                    instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
